On Tue, 27 Apr 2004, Rick wrote:

> Bizarre...the only thing I can imagine where hissing in the cab could be
> related to engine trouble is a vacuum leak:
>
>  1) Do you have an aftermarket vacuum gauge? Maybe the hose is coming
> loose
>
> 2) The brake booster is vacuum powered and is located under the cab on
> older buses (not sure about an '80), but if it or it's hose leaked, you
> would notice hard braking as well

That sounds like the mostly likely explanation -- braking has been getting 
harder over the past week or so.

